trans-unit.source: Implements the basic functionality for a personalization provider.
trans-unit.target: Implementerer den grunnleggende funksjonaliteten for en leverandør av personlige data.

trans-unit.source: This is the abstract base class that defines the required functionality of a personalization provider.
trans-unit.target: Dette er abstrakt basisklasse som definerer den nødvendige funksjonaliteten for en leverandør av personlige data.

trans-unit.source: A personalization provider both loads and stores personalization data on behalf of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization> instance.
trans-unit.target: Leverandør av personlige data både laster inn og lagrer personlige data på vegne av en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization>forekomsten.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization>

trans-unit.source: The base class defines standard behavior for a number of methods; only those methods that specifically deal with the underlying data store are marked abstract.
trans-unit.target: Basisklassen definerer standard virkemåte for en rekke måter; bare metoder som spesifikt gjelder underliggende datalager merkes abstrakt.

trans-unit.source: This allows a developer to write a custom provider to interact with a specific data store, without needing to re-implement standard functionality used by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization> class.
trans-unit.target: Dette gjør det mulig for utviklere å skrive egendefinerte leverandøren for å bruke et bestemt datalager uten å måtte implementere på nytt standard funksjoner som brukes av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization>klasse.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationProvider"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationProvider"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Because this is a constructor for an abstract class, you must override this method to create an instance of a class that inherits from this class.
trans-unit.target: Fordi dette er en konstruktør for en abstrakt klasse, må du overstyre denne metoden hvis du vil opprette en forekomst av klassen som arver fra denne klassen.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets or sets the name of the application configured for the provider.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter eller angir navnet på programmet som er konfigurert for leverandøren.

trans-unit.source: If an application name is not specified in the configuration file using the [providers Element for personalization for webParts (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/51363b49-eafa-4b9c-b9d0-80086b385195) attribute, the value of the <xref:System.Web.Hosting.HostingEnvironment.ApplicationVirtualPath%2A> property is used.
trans-unit.target: Hvis navnet på programmet ikke er angitt i konfigurasjonen filen med den [leverandører elementet for tilpassing webdeler (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/51363b49-eafa-4b9c-b9d0-80086b385195) attributt, verdien for den <xref:System.Web.Hosting.HostingEnvironment.ApplicationVirtualPath%2A>egenskapen brukes.</xref:System.Web.Hosting.HostingEnvironment.ApplicationVirtualPath%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!CAUTION] > Because a single, default personalization provider instance is used for all the requests served by an <xref:System.Web.HttpApplication> object, you can have multiple requests executing concurrently, each attempting to set the ApplicationName property value.
trans-unit.target: > [!CAUTION] > Fordi én standardforekomsten personlige data provider brukes for alle forespørsler som behandles av en <xref:System.Web.HttpApplication>objektet, du kan ha flere forespørsler som utføres samtidig, hver forsøk på å angi egenskapsverdien ApplicationName.</xref:System.Web.HttpApplication>

trans-unit.source: The ApplicationName property is not thread-safe for multiple writes, and changing the ApplicationName property value can result in unexpected behavior for multiple users of an application.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen ApplicationName er ikke sikker for flere skriver, og endre egenskapsverdien ApplicationName kan føre til uventede resultater for flere brukere med en applikasjon.

trans-unit.source: It is recommended that you avoid code allowing users to set the ApplicationName property unless required.
trans-unit.target: Det anbefales at du unngår kode som tillater brukere å angi egenskapen ApplicationName hvis nødvendig.

trans-unit.source: Setting the ApplicationName property might be required, for example, in an administrative application that manages personalization data for multiple applications.
trans-unit.target: Angi egenskapen ApplicationName kan være nødvendig, for eksempel i et administrative program som behandler personlige data for flere programmer.

trans-unit.source: The application configured for the personalization provider.
trans-unit.target: Programmet er konfigurert for bruk av personlige data leverandøren.

trans-unit.source: Currently, this method returns a list containing two capabilities: <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.ModifyStateUserCapability>.
trans-unit.target: For øyeblikket metoden returnerer en liste som inneholder to muligheter: <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability>og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.ModifyStateUserCapability>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.ModifyStateUserCapability> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability>

trans-unit.source: These are the default capabilities that can be defined in the [authorization Element for personalization for webParts (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d190d4ff-1445-4ee1-88eb-9737c7aa1434) element within the [personalization Element for webParts (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/3d77da55-73ce-46ce-97cf-7d2abcaada09) element of the[webParts Element (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/90af5acc-5a80-4b39-bba7-74afd06b167c) configuration section.
trans-unit.target: Dette er standard funksjonene som kan defineres i den [godkjenning elementet for tilpassing webdeler (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d190d4ff-1445-4ee1-88eb-9737c7aa1434) elementet i den [tilpassing elementet webdeler (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/3d77da55-73ce-46ce-97cf-7d2abcaada09) element av den[webdeler elementet (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/90af5acc-5a80-4b39-bba7-74afd06b167c) konfigurasjonsdelen.

trans-unit.source: If you choose to implement a custom personalization infrastructure, you can override this method and define your own set of authorization-related user capabilities.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du velger å implementere en egendefinert tilpassing-infrastruktur, kan du kan overstyre denne metoden og definere ditt eget sett med authorization-relaterte bruker funksjoner.

trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Collections.IList>som representerer sett med kjente funksjoner som brukes av webdeler kontrollen settet.</xref:System.Collections.IList>

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the initial personalization scope should be <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope"></xref> or <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope"></xref> scope.
trans-unit.target: Bestemmer om det opprinnelige området må være <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope"> </xref> eller <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope"> </xref> omfanget.

trans-unit.source: This method determines whether the current scope should be <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>, given a reference to a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control and the personalization state information that has already been loaded from earlier in the personalization life cycle.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden bestemmer om det skal være gjeldende omfang <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>eller <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>, angitt en referanse til en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontrollen og tilpassing tilstandsinformasjon som er allerede lastet inn fra tidligere i tilpassing livssyklus.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: This information is used by a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization> instance for subsequent personalization-related tasks.
trans-unit.target: Denne informasjonen brukes av en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization>forekomsten for senere bruk av personlige data relatert oppgaver.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization>

trans-unit.source: The following rules are used to determine personalization scope: - Scope is assumed initially to be <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.
trans-unit.target: Følgende regler brukes til å fastsette område:-område er opprinnelig antatt for å være <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: - If the currently executing user account is not authenticated, the scope is set to <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis øyeblikket kjøres brukerkontoen ikke er godkjent, er området satt til <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: - If the currently executing user account is authenticated, additional processing occurs in order of precedence: - If the page is in postback mode, the page request contains scope information from a previous rendering of the page.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis øyeblikket kjøres brukerkontoen er godkjent, ytterligere behandling forekommer i rekkefølgen:-Hvis siden er i modus for sende tilbake, side-forespørselen inneholder informasjon om omfang fra en tidligere gjengivelse av siden.

trans-unit.source: If that scope information indicates that <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope was used, then the scope evaluates to <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis som område informasjon som angir at <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfanget ble brukt, og deretter omfanget evalueres til <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: - If the currently executing page had control transferred to it from another page (for example, if the transfer of control occurred due to calling the <xref:System.Web.HttpServerUtility.Transfer%2A> method; note that this specific check does not occur for cross-page posting), and if the previously executing page had a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> instance, the scope is set to the value of the `Personalization.Scope` property from the previous <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> instance.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis siden for øyeblikket kjøres hadde kontroll overført til den fra en annen side (Hvis for eksempel overføring av kontrollen oppstod på grunn av kaller den <xref:System.Web.HttpServerUtility.Transfer%2A>metoden; Obs denne bestemte kontrollen ikke finnes for postering på tvers av sider), og hvis tidligere kjøres siden har en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>forekomsten området er satt til verdien for den `Personalization.Scope` egenskapen fra forrige <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>forekomsten.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.HttpServerUtility.Transfer%2A>

trans-unit.source: - If the previous criteria are not met, then the scope evaluates to the value of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.InitialScope%2A> property for the current <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis tidligere vilkårene ikke er oppfylt, deretter omfanget returnerer verdien for den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.InitialScope%2A>egenskapen for gjeldende <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.InitialScope%2A>

trans-unit.source: After the previous evaluations have been made, and if the scope evaluates to <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, the following processing occurs: - If the currently executing user account has the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability> capability, the scope remains set to <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.
trans-unit.target: Når de forrige evalueringer er utført, og hvis omfanget evalueres til <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>område, skjer følgende behandling: – Hvis øyeblikket kjøres brukerkontoen har <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability>funksjonen, omfanget forblir settes til <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: - If the currently executing user account does not have the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability> capability, then the scope is reset to <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis i øyeblikket kjøres brukerkontoen ikke har <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability>funksjonen, og området er tilbakestilt til <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability>

trans-unit.source: - If the result of all previous scope evaluations is <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>, this result is stored as a hidden field on the currently executing page.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis resultatet av alle tidligere omfanget evalueringer <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>, dette resultatet lagres som et skjult felt i øyeblikket kjøres siden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: This is the mechanism whereby a page can replay the scope evaluation during subsequent postbacks.
trans-unit.target: Dette er mekanisme der en side kan spille omfanget evalueringen under etterfølgende tilbakesendinger.

trans-unit.source: Returns a dictionary containing <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartUserCapability"></xref> instances that represent the personalization-related capabilities of the currently executing user account.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en liste som inneholder <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartUserCapability"> </xref> forekomstene som representerer personlige data relatert mulighetene for øyeblikket kjøres brukerkontoen.

trans-unit.source: The default implementation of this method consumes the information in the [authorization Element for personalization for webParts (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d190d4ff-1445-4ee1-88eb-9737c7aa1434) element within the [personalization Element for webParts (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/3d77da55-73ce-46ce-97cf-7d2abcaada09) element of the[webParts Element (ASP.NET Settings Schema)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/90af5acc-5a80-4b39-bba7-74afd06b167c) configuration section in the Machine.config or Web.config file to determine a user's authorized capabilities.
trans-unit.target: Standard implementering av denne metoden bruker informasjonen i den [godkjenning elementet for tilpassing webdeler (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d190d4ff-1445-4ee1-88eb-9737c7aa1434) elementet i den [tilpassing elementet webdeler (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/3d77da55-73ce-46ce-97cf-7d2abcaada09) element av den[webdeler elementet (ASP.NET innstillingsskjemaet)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/90af5acc-5a80-4b39-bba7-74afd06b167c) konfigurasjonsdelen i Machine.config eller Web.config-filen for å finne en bruker er godkjent funksjoner.

trans-unit.source: The capabilities in the dictionary will be members of the <xref:System.Collections.IList> object returned by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationProvider.CreateSupportedUserCapabilities%2A> method, which currently include the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability> capability and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.ModifyStateUserCapability> capability.
trans-unit.target: Funksjonene i ordlisten blir medlemmer av den <xref:System.Collections.IList>objektet som ble returnert av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationProvider.CreateSupportedUserCapabilities%2A>metoden, som for øyeblikket inkluderer den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability>funksjonen og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.ModifyStateUserCapability>funksjonen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.ModifyStateUserCapability> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartPersonalization.EnterSharedScopeUserCapability> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationProvider.CreateSupportedUserCapabilities%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IList>

trans-unit.target: Returnerer en samling som inneholder null eller flere når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo"> </xref>-avledet objekter basert på omfanget og bestemte spørringsparametere.

trans-unit.source: This method is the abstract definition of an administrative method for querying personalization data.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden er abstrakt definisjonen av en administrative metode for spørring personlige data.

trans-unit.source: Derived implementations should follow the logic described below.
trans-unit.target: Avledede implementeringer bør følge logikken beskrevet nedenfor.

trans-unit.source: The set of returned items is constrained by the `pageIndex` and `pageSize` parameters, where `pageSize` sets the number of records to return and `pageIndex` sets which records to return.
trans-unit.target: Settet med returnerte elementer er begrenset av den `pageIndex` og `pageSize` parametere, der `pageSize` angir antall poster som skal returneres og `pageIndex` angir hvilke poster som skal returneres.

trans-unit.source: For example, a `pageIndex` of 0 and a `pageSize` of 25 would return the first 25 occurrences, while a `pageIndex` of 1 and a `pageSize` of 25 would return occurrences 26-50.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel en `pageIndex` 0 og en `pageSize` for 25 returnerer de første 25 forekomstene under en `pageIndex` 1 og en `pageSize` for 25 returnerer forekomster 26 50.

trans-unit.source: If you want to retrieve all available records, set `pageIndex` to 0 and `pageSize` to <xref:System.Int32.MaxValue>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil hente alle tilgjengelige poster, angi `pageIndex` 0 og `pageSize` til <xref:System.Int32.MaxValue>.</xref:System.Int32.MaxValue>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo>-derived objects are returned in alphabetical order and sorted by a combination of their <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo.Path%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.UserPersonalizationStateInfo.Username%2A> property values, both in ascending order.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo>-avledede objekter ble returnert alfabetisk og sortert etter en kombinasjon av deres <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo.Path%2A>og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.UserPersonalizationStateInfo.Username%2A>egenskapen verdier, i stigende rekkefølge.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.UserPersonalizationStateInfo.Username%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo.Path%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateInfo>

trans-unit.source: This method passes query wildcard characters to the underlying data store.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden sender spørringen jokertegn til den underliggende datakilden.

trans-unit.source: Support for wildcard characters is currently dependent on how each provider handles characters such as an asterisk (*), a percent symbol (%), or an underscore (_).
trans-unit.target: Støtte for jokertegn er for øyeblikket er avhengig av hvordan hver leverandøren håndterer tegn som en stjerne (*), en prosent symbolet (%) eller et understrekingstegn (_).

trans-unit.source: Normally, for SQL-compliant data stores, you can perform a wildcard search on a partial path with the wildcard character appearing at the beginning, the end, or the middle of the search string text in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.PathToMatch%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Vanligvis for SQL-kompatibel data butikker, kan du utføre en søk med jokertegn i en delvis banen med jokertegnet vises på begynnelsen, slutten eller midt i strengen søketeksten i den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.PathToMatch%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.PathToMatch%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, to find all paths that start with "~/vdir", the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.PathToMatch%2A> property would be set to "~/vdir%".
trans-unit.target: For eksempel for å finne alle baner som begynner med "~/vdir" i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.PathToMatch%2A>vil være satt til "~/vdir%".</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.PathToMatch%2A>

trans-unit.source: Likewise, a wildcard search on a partial user name could have the wildcard character appear at any point in the text string of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.UsernameToMatch%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: På samme måte et jokertegn Søk etter en delvis brukernavn kan ha jokertegnet vises når som helst i tekststreng med den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.UsernameToMatch%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationStateQuery.UsernameToMatch%2A>
